#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:2
msgid "v2 Migration Guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:4
msgid ""
"**urllib3 2.x is now available!** Read below for how to get started and what "
"is contained in the new major release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:7
msgid "**🚀 Migrating from 1.x to 2.x**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:9
msgid ""
"We're maintaining **functional API compatibility for most users** to make "
"the migration an easy choice for almost everyone. Most changes are either to "
"default configurations, supported Python versions, or internal "
"implementation details. So unless you're in a specific situation you should "
"notice no changes! 🎉"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:16
msgid ""
"If you have difficulty migrating to 2.x or following this guide you can "
"`open an issue on GitHub <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues>`_ or "
"reach out in `our community Discord channel <https://discord.gg/urllib3>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:22
msgid "What are the important changes?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:24
msgid ""
"Here's a short summary of which changes in urllib3 2.x are most important:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:26
msgid ""
"Python version must be **3.10 or later** (previously supported Python 2.7, "
"and 3.5 to 3.9)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:27
msgid ""
"Removed support for non-OpenSSL TLS libraries (like LibreSSL and wolfSSL)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:28
msgid "Removed support for OpenSSL versions older than 1.1.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:29
msgid ""
"Removed support for Python implementations that aren't CPython or PyPy3 "
"(previously supported Google App Engine, Jython)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:30
msgid "Removed the ``urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool`` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:31
msgid "Removed the ``urllib3.contrib.securetransport`` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:32
msgid "Removed the ``urllib3[secure]`` extra."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:33
msgid ""
"Deprecated URLs without a scheme (ie 'https://') and will be raising an "
"error in a future version of urllib3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:34
msgid ""
"Changed the default minimum TLS version to TLS 1.2 (previously was TLS 1.0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:35
msgid "Changed the default request body encoding from 'ISO-8859-1' to 'UTF-8'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:36
msgid ""
"Removed support for verifying certificate hostnames via ``commonName``, now "
"only ``subjectAltName`` is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:37
msgid ""
"Removed the default set of TLS ciphers, instead now urllib3 uses the list of "
"ciphers configured by the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:39
msgid ""
"For a full list of changes you can look at `the changelog <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/blob/main/CHANGES.rst>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:44
msgid "Sunsetting urllib3 1.26.x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:46
msgid ""
"urllib3 1.26.x is not currently maintained. urllib3 2.x is the best version "
"of urllib3 and is widely supported by the larger Python ecosystem. That "
"said, urllib3 1.26.x still sees significant download numbers, mainly because "
"the botocore package still requires urllib3 1.26.x for Python 3.9 and "
"earlier. If your organization would benefit from the continued support of "
"urllib3 1.26.x, please contact sethmichaellarson@gmail.com to discuss "
"sponsorship or contribution opportunities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:53
msgid ""
"However, upgrading is still recommended as **no new feature developments or "
"fixes will be shipped to the 1.26.x release stream**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:57
msgid "**🤔 Common upgrading issues**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:60
msgid "ssl module is compiled with OpenSSL 1.0.2.k-fips"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:62
msgid ""
"ImportError: urllib3 v2 only supports OpenSSL 1.1.1+, currently the 'ssl' "
"module is compiled with 'OpenSSL 1.0.2k-fips  26 Jan 2017'.\n"
"See: https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2168"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:67
msgid "Remediation depends on your system:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:69
msgid ""
"**AWS Lambda**: Upgrade to the Python 3.10 (or later) runtime as it uses "
"OpenSSL 1.1.1. Alternatively, you can use a `custom Docker image <https://"
"aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/new-for-aws-lambda-container-image-support/>`_ and "
"ensure you use a Python build that uses OpenSSL 1.1.1 or later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:73
msgid ""
"**Amazon Linux 2**: Upgrade to `Amazon Linux 2023 <https://aws.amazon.com/"
"linux/amazon-linux-2023/>`_. Alternatively, you can install OpenSSL 1.1.1 on "
"Amazon Linux 2 using ``yum install openssl11 openssl11-devel`` and then "
"install Python with a tool like pyenv."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:77
msgid "**Red Hat Enterpritse Linux 7 (RHEL 7)**: Upgrade to RHEL 8 or later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:78
msgid ""
"**Read the Docs**: Upgrade your `configuration file to use Ubuntu 22.04 "
"<https://docs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/config-file/v2.html>`_ by using ``os: "
"ubuntu-22.04`` in the ``build`` section. Feel free to use the `urllib3 "
"configuration <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/blob/2.0.0/.readthedocs."
"yml>`_ as an inspiration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:84
msgid ""
"docker.errors.dockerexception: error while fetching server api version: "
"request() got an unexpected keyword argument 'chunked'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:86
msgid "Upgrade to ``docker==6.1.0`` that is compatible with urllib3 2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:89
msgid ""
"ImportError: cannot import name 'gaecontrib' from 'requests_toolbelt._compat'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:91
msgid ""
"To be compatible with urllib3 2.0, Requests Toolbelt released version 1.0.0 "
"without Google App Engine Standard Python 2.7 support. Most users that "
"reported this issue were using the `Pyrebase <https://github.com/thisbejim/"
"Pyrebase>`_ library that provides an API for the Firebase API. This library "
"is unmaintained, but `replacements exist <https://github.com/thisbejim/"
"Pyrebase/issues/435>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:98
msgid ""
"``ImportError: cannot import name 'DEFAULT_CIPHERS' from 'urllib3.util."
"ssl_'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:100
msgid ""
"This likely happens because you're using botocore which `does not support "
"urllib3 2.0 yet <https://github.com/boto/botocore/issues/2921>`_. The good "
"news is that botocore explicitly declares in its dependencies that it only "
"supports ``urllib3<2``. Make sure to use a recent pip. That way, pip will "
"install urllib3 1.26.x for versions of botocore that do not support urllib3 "
"2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:105
msgid ""
"If you're deploying to an AWS environment such as Lambda with the Python 3.9 "
"runtime or a host using Amazon Linux 2, you'll need to explicitly pin to "
"``urllib3<2`` in your project to ensure urllib3 2.0 isn't brought into your "
"environment. Otherwise, this may result in unintended side effects with the "
"default boto3 installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:111
msgid ""
"AttributeError: module 'urllib3.connectionpool' has no attribute "
"'VerifiedHTTPSConnection'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:113
msgid ""
"The ``VerifiedHTTPSConnection`` class has always been documented to be in "
"the :mod:`~urllib3.connection` module. It used to be possible to import it "
"from :mod:`~urllib3.connectionpool` but that was acccidental and is no "
"longer possible due to a refactoring in urllib3 2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:118
msgid ""
"Note that the new name of this class is :class:`~urllib3.connection."
"HTTPSConnection`. It can be used starting from urllib3 1.25.9."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:122
msgid "AttributeError: 'HTTPResponse' object has no attribute 'strict'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:124
msgid ""
"The ``strict`` parameter is unneeded with Python 3 and should be removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:129
msgid "Migrating as an application developer?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:131
msgid ""
"If you're someone who writes Python but doesn't ship as a package (things "
"like web services, data science, tools, and more) this section is for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:133
msgid ""
"Python environments only allow for one version of a dependency to be "
"installed per environment which means that **all of your dependencies using "
"urllib3 need to support 2.x for you to upgrade**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:136
msgid ""
"The best way to visualize relationships between your dependencies is using "
"`pipdeptree <https://pypi.org/project/pipdeptree>`_ and ``$ pipdeptree --"
"reverse``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:138
msgid ""
"# From inside your Python environment:\n"
"$ python -m pip install pipdeptree\n"
"# We only care about packages requiring urllib3\n"
"$ pipdeptree --reverse | grep \"requires: urllib3\"\n"
"├── botocore==1.38.36 [requires: urllib3>=1.25.4,<1.27]\n"
"└── requests==2.32.4 [requires: urllib3>=1.21.1,<3]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:147
msgid ""
"Reading the output from above, there are two packages which depend on "
"urllib3: ``botocore`` and ``requests``. While requests supports urllib3 2.x "
"(with the ``<3`` specified), botocore requires urllib3 1.26.x (with the "
"``<1.27`` version specifier). Note that botocore does support urllib3 2.x, "
"but it only supports it on Python 3.10 and later, which mandates OpenSSL "
"1.1.1+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:151
msgid ""
"It's important to know `urllib3 does not receive security fixes at the "
"moment <#sunsetting-urllib3-1-26-x>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:155
msgid "Migrating as a package maintainer?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:157
msgid ""
"If you're a maintainer of a package that uses urllib3 under the hood then "
"this section is for you. You may have already seen an issue opened from "
"someone on our team about the upcoming release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:160
msgid ""
"The primary goal for migrating to urllib3 2.x should be to ensure your "
"package supports **both urllib3 v1.26.x and 2.x for some time**. This is to "
"reduce the chance that diamond dependencies are introduced into your users' "
"dependencies which will then cause issues with them upgrading to the latest "
"version of **your package**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:164
msgid ""
"The first step to supporting urllib3 2.x is to make sure the version 2.x not "
"being excluded by ``install_requires``. You should ensure your package "
"allows for both urllib3 1.26.x and 2.x to be used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:167
msgid ""
"# setup.py (setuptools)\n"
"setup(\n"
"  ...\n"
"  install_requires=[\"urllib3>=1.26,<3\"]\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"# pyproject.toml (hatch)\n"
"[project]\n"
"dependencies = [\n"
"  \"urllib3>=1.26,<3\"\n"
"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:181
msgid ""
"Next you should try installing urllib3 v2.x locally and run your test suite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:183
msgid "$ python -m pip install -U 'urllib3>=2'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:187
msgid ""
"Because there are new ``FutureWarnings`` you should ensure that you're able "
"to see those warnings when running your test suite. To do so you can add the "
"following to your test setup to ensure even ``FutureWarnings`` are output to "
"the terminal:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:192
msgid ""
"# Set PYTHONWARNING=default to show all warnings.\n"
"$ export PYTHONWARNINGS=\"default\"\n"
"\n"
"# Run your test suite and look for failures.\n"
"# Pytest automatically prints all warnings.\n"
"$ pytest tests/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:201
msgid "or you can opt-in within your Python code:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:203
msgid ""
"# You can change warning filters according to the filter rules:\n"
"# https://docs.python.org/3/library/warnings.html#warning-filter\n"
"import warnings\n"
"warnings.filterwarnings(\"default\", category=FutureWarning)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:210
msgid ""
"Any failures or deprecation warnings you receive should be fixed as urllib3 "
"v3.0 will remove all deprecated features. Many deprecation warnings will "
"make suggestions about what to do to avoid the deprecated feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:213
msgid "Warnings will look something like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:215
msgid ""
"FutureWarning: 'ssl_version' option is deprecated and will be removed\n"
"in urllib3 v3.0. Instead use 'ssl_minimum_version'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:220
msgid ""
"Continue removing deprecation warnings until there are no more. After this "
"you can publish a new release of your package that supports both urllib3 "
"1.26.x and 2.x."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:225
msgid ""
"If you're not able to support both 1.26.x and 2.x of urllib3 at the same "
"time with your package please `open an issue on GitHub <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues>`_ or reach out in `our community Discord channel "
"<https://discord.gg/urllib3>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:231
msgid "**💪 User-friendly features**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:233
msgid ""
"urllib3 has always billed itself as a **user-friendly HTTP client library**. "
"In the spirit of being even more user-friendly we've added two features "
"which should make using urllib3 for tinkering sessions, throw-away scripts, "
"and smaller projects a breeze!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:239
msgid "urllib3.request()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:241
msgid ""
"Previously the highest-level API available for urllib3 was a "
"``PoolManager``, but for many cases configuring a poolmanager is extra steps "
"for no benefit. To make using urllib3 as simple as possible we've added a "
"top-level function for sending requests from a global poolmanager instance:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:246
msgid ""
">>> import urllib3\n"
">>> resp = urllib3.request(\"GET\", \"https://example.com\")\n"
">>> resp.status\n"
"200"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:254
msgid "JSON support for requests and responses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:256
msgid "JSON is everywhere – and now it's in urllib3, too!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:258
msgid ""
"If you'd like to send JSON in a request body or deserialize a response body "
"from JSON into Python objects you can now use the new ``json=`` parameter "
"for requests and ``HTTPResponse.json()`` method on responses:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:262
msgid ""
"import urllib3\n"
"\n"
"# Send a request with a JSON body.\n"
"# This adds 'Content-Type: application/json' by default.\n"
"resp = urllib3.request(\n"
"    \"POST\", \"https://example.api.com\",\n"
"    json={\"key\": \"value\"}\n"
")\n"
"\n"
"# Receive a JSON body in the response.\n"
"resp = urllib3.request(\"GET\", \"https://xkcd.com/2347/info.0.json\")\n"
"\n"
"# There's always an XKCD...\n"
"resp.json()\n"
"{\n"
"  \"num\": 2347,\n"
"  \"img\": \"https://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/dependency.png\",\n"
"  \"title\": \"Dependency\",\n"
"  ...\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:287
msgid "**✨ Optimized for Python 3.10+**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:289
msgid ""
"urllib3 2.x specifically targets CPython 3.10+ and PyPy 7.3.17+ (compatible "
"with CPython 3.10) and dropping support for Python versions 2.7, and 3.5 to "
"3.9."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:292
msgid ""
"By dropping end-of-life Python versions we're able to optimize the codebase "
"for Python 3.10+ by using new features to improve performance and reduce the "
"amount of code that needs to be executed in order to support legacy versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:299
msgid "**📜 Type-hinted APIs**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:301
msgid ""
"You're finally able to run Mypy or other type-checkers on code using "
"urllib3. This also means that for IDEs that support type hints you'll "
"receive better suggestions from auto-complete. No more confusion with "
"``**kwargs``!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:306
msgid ""
"We've also added API interfaces like ``BaseHTTPResponse`` and "
"``BaseHTTPConnection`` to ensure that when you're sub-classing an interface "
"you're only using supported public APIs to ensure compatibility and minimize "
"breakages down the road."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:313
msgid ""
"If you're one of the rare few who is subclassing connections or responses "
"you should take a closer look at detailed changes in `the changelog <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/blob/main/CHANGES.rst>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:319
msgid "**🔐 Modern security by default**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:322
msgid "HTTPS requires TLS 1.2+"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:324
msgid ""
"Greater than 95% of websites support TLS 1.2 or above. At this point we're "
"comfortable switching the default minimum TLS version to be 1.2 to ensure "
"high security for users without breaking services."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:329
msgid ""
"Dropping TLS 1.0 and 1.1 by default means you won't be vulnerable to TLS "
"downgrade attacks if a vulnerability in TLS 1.0 or 1.1 were discovered in "
"the future. Extra security for free! By dropping TLS 1.0 and TLS 1.1 we also "
"tighten the list of ciphers we need to support to ensure high security for "
"data traveling over the wire."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:337
msgid ""
"If you still need to use TLS 1.0 or 1.1 in your application you can still "
"upgrade to v2.x, you'll only need to set ``ssl_minimum_version`` to the "
"proper value to continue using legacy TLS versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:344
msgid "Stop verifying commonName in certificates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:346
msgid ""
"Dropping support the long deprecated ``commonName`` field on certificates in "
"favor of only verifying ``subjectAltName`` to put us in line with browsers "
"and other HTTP client libraries and to improve security for our users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:353
msgid "Certificate verification via SSLContext"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../v2-migration-guide.rst:355
msgid ""
"By default certificate verification is handled by urllib3 to support legacy "
"Python versions, but now we can rely on Python's certificate verification "
"instead! This should result in a speedup for verifying certificates and "
"means that any improvements made to certificate verification in Python or "
"OpenSSL will be immediately available."
msgstr ""
